learning_outcomes.en:
· can facilitate the full project cycle, from ideation to project delivery and reporting, including goal-setting and related KPI-s, prioritisation, risk management;
· knows the specific tools and methods used in project management, and can accommodate varying needs and diverse situations, based on project specifics;
· has knowledge of project management in the creative domain, including managing a project team, organising the workflow and overseeing project finances, working with partners and stakeholders, addressing marketing and sales;
· understands global and creative industry trends, and is able to put together a value proposition aimed at specific audiences, in a meaningful and impactful way;
· can ask questions specific to the field and argue their point, including taking part in discussions with specialists;
· has a overview of domain-specific literature, and can formulate the problems faced in daily work in written form, is able to analyze them and draw conclusions;
